# API request URL and parameters
url = "https://api.tequila.kiwi.com/v2/search"

# Headers for the API request
headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "apikey": " api key "  
}

# Define CSV columns
csv_columns = [
    "flight_number",
    "airline_code",
    "origin",
    "destination",
    "departure_time",
    "arrival_time",
    "duration",
    "price"
]

# Write flight data to a CSV file
with open("finalprojeccsv", mode="w", newline="") as csvfile:
    writer = csv.DictWriter(csvfile, fieldnames=csv_columns)
    writer.writeheader()

    # Iterate through pages of results
    for page in range(1, 1001):
        params = {
            "fly_from": "LON",
            "fly_to": "CDG,ORY,LYS,NCE,SXB,RNS,BIA,AJA,MPL,BIQ,EGC,LIL,ETZ,MAD,BCN,AGP,ALC,ACE,FUE,TFS,LPA,TFN,GRO,OVD,BIO,VLC,SVQ,PMI,SCQ,SDR,ZAZ,VGO,MJV,RMU,LIS,OPO,FAO,FNC,PDL,TER,HOR,PIX,SMA,BLQ,CIA,CTA,FCO,LIN,MXP,NAP,PSA,TRN,VCE,AHO,AOI,BDS,BRI,CAG,CTG,EBA,FRL,FLR,LMP,PMO,REG,SUF,TPS,VBS,PSA,BZO,LCC,PSR,TRS,VRN,FRA,MUC,STR,DUS,HAJ,DRS,BRE,ERF,SCN,PAD,IST,SAW,AYT,ADB,ESB,DLM,ADA,GZP,BJV,TZX,DIY,VAN,HTY,ASR,NAV,KYA,SZF,DLM,MLX,EZS,IZM,ATH,SKG,HER,RHO,CHQ,CFU,JTR,JMK,KGS,EFL,ZTH,JSI,SMI,AXD,KVA,KLX,IOA,MJT,VIE,INN,GRZ,LNZ,KLU,ZAG,SPU,DBV,ZAD,PUY,RJK,OSI,WAW,WMI,GDN,KTW,KRK,LCJ,LUZ,RZE,DEB,SOB,PEV,QGY,SOF,VAR,BOJ,PDV,EIN,GRQ,TIA,OTP,CLJ,TSR,IAS,CND,SBZ,BCM,CRA,TGM,BRU,OST,LGG,ANR,PRG,BRQ,OSR,KLV,PED,ARN,BMA,MMX,LLA,KRN,UME,OSD,SFT,VBY,SDL,ZRH,BSL,BRN,LUG,ODE,RNN,EBJ,KRP,SGD,HEL,OUL,RVN,TKU,TMP,VAA,KUO,BTS,KSC,TAT,BGO,SVG,TRD,TOS,KRS,AES,EVE,BOO,MOL,HAU,BFS,BHD,NOC,SJJ,BNX,OMO,TZL,VNO,KUN,PLQ,LJU,MBX,RIX,LPX,TLL,AEY,KEF,LUX,BZG,SZY,IBZ,BGY,DUB,NTE,RDZ,POZ,AAL,SZZ,FMM,ORK,NOC,TLS,VXO,FNI,BOD,BVE,LIG,KIR,MST,SNN,MRS,GVA,DTM,CGN,PIS,HHN,FKB,TUF,AAR,LRH,BRE,GNB,HAM,CPH,GOT,LEJ,BLL,NUE,BUD,AMS,RTM,BZR,VRN,RMI ",
            "date_from": "01/04/2023",
            "date_to": "28/02/2024",
            "offset": (page - 1) * 100,  # Update the offset for each page
            "limit": 100  # Limit results per page    
        }
            
        

        # Make the API request
        response = requests.get(url, params=params, headers=headers)

        # Parse the API response
        flight_data = json.loads(response.text)

        # Iterate through flight data and write to the CSV file
        for flight in flight_data["data"]:
            flight_number = flight["route"][0]["flight_no"]
            airline_code = flight["route"][0]["airline"]
            origin = flight["route"][0]["flyFrom"]
            destination = flight["route"][-1]["flyTo"]
            departure_time = flight["route"][0]["utc_departure"]
            arrival_time = flight["route"][-1]["utc_arrival"]
            duration = flight["duration"]["total"]  # assuming the duration is available as "total" in the "duration" field
            distance = flight["distance"]  # assuming the distance is available in the "distance" field
            price = flight["price"]

            writer.writerow({
                "flight_number": flight_number,
                "airline_code": airline_code,
                "origin": origin,
                "destination": destination,
                "departure_time": departure_time,
                "arrival_time": arrival_time,
                "duration": duration,
                "price": price
            })

        # Add a delay between requests to respect the API rate limit
        if page % 30 == 0:
            time.sleep(60)

# create a function to map specific hours of the day to the desired time frame categories
# and apply this both to departure and arrival in DF

# Function to map hours to time frame categories
def hour_to_time_frame(hour):
    if 0 <= hour < 4:
        return "Late Night"
    elif 4 <= hour < 8:
        return "Early Morning"
    elif 8 <= hour < 12:
        return "Morning"
    elif 12 <= hour < 16:
        return "Afternoon"
    elif 16 <= hour < 20:
        return "Evening"
    else:
        return "Night"

# Read the CSV file
filtered_df = pd.read_csv('filtered_with_days_left.csv', parse_dates=['departure_time', 'arrival_time'])

# Apply the function to 'departure_time' and 'arrival_time' columns
filtered_df['departure_time_frame'] = filtered_df['departure_time'].dt.hour.apply(hour_to_time_frame)
filtered_df['arrival_time_frame'] = filtered_df['arrival_time'].dt.hour.apply(hour_to_time_frame)

# Save the DataFrame back to a new CSV file
filtered_df.to_csv('filtered_with_days_left_and_time_frames.csv', index=False)

departure_time_frame_dummies = pd.get_dummies(df['departure_time_frame'], prefix='departure_time')
